Beechview PA Locksmith Store also provides security consultations for free. You can call us on 412-407-6859 to request our professional locksmiths in Spring Hill City View to visit your property and have them suggest upgrades to your security.<|end_of_text|>Flash a little personality with these ballerina flats. For exuberant mums and their girls, these shoes come in mini sizes and feature a large crystal embellishment alongside fluffy pom-poms. Glitzy and glamourous, the sparkly shoes capture light on its textured glitter material.<|end_of_text|>There’s a strong chance Portage County is making the trip to Salem.
The top half of the Division III Salem bracket is loaded with Portage County teams, with No. 1 Waterloo and No. 4 Mogadore earning first-round byes and potentially in line to face each other in a March 4 district semifinal.
There could be a Portage Trail Conference County Division rematch beforehand.
No. 5 Rootstown is set to host No. 12 Crestview in a Feb. 26 first-round game. A win would send the Rovers back to Mogadore, where they fell 72-57 Friday night. The Rovers won the teams’ first meeting back in Rootstown.
It would be the latest in an epic rivalry as the Rovers and Wildcats have also squared off for the County Division football title two years running, with many of the same kids taking the hardwood as the gridiron.
The Bombers could also be headed for a rematch. Should No. 5 Windham get past No. 13 Bloomfield Feb. 26, it would play host to No. 5 Newbury in a March 1 sectional final. The Bombers lost their season opener to the Black Knights before beating them by six later in the season.
Back to the Portage Trail Conference, No. 6 Crestwood will play host to No. 11 Brooklyn Feb. 26, and would travel to No. 3 Elyria Catholic March 1 with a win. The Panthers are 10-7 and only got 11 more votes than the Red Devils in the seeding voting.
No. 7 Garfield will be favored against No. 10 Grand Valley, which struggled mightily against Crestwood and Windham teams that the G-Men beat this season, but would then be an underdog in a potential March 1 sectional final against second-seeded LaBrae. The Vikings eliminated the G-Men last year and took a 76-70 victory in Garrettsville earlier this season.
In the Metro Division, Streetsboro’s strong conference season hasn’t been ignored. The Rockets have challenged themselves with a tough non-conference schedule (leading to a 1-6 non-conference record), while compiling an 8-5 Metro mark. They were rewarded with a Division II Stow first-round game in Streetsboro Feb. 26, as the eighth-seeded Rockets play host to No. 9 Orange. The reward for winning? A March 1 date with Hunter Drenth and the Revere Minutemen.
Also in the Division II Stow district, No. 11 Ravenna makes the trip to No. 6 Chagrin Falls, and No. 13 Southeast, still seeking its first win of the season, has a cross-division first-round date with No. 4 Woodridge, this year’s Metro Division champion. The Bulldogs are balanced as can be — and on a serious tear, having won 10 straight games.
Woodridge’s Tuesday opponent, Aurora, earned the No. 7 seed and will host No. 10 Cleveland John F. Kennedy Feb. 26. The winner gets No. 2 Gilmour Academy.
The Falcons join Metro rivals Coventry, Norton and Springfield in the Division II Canton district, with No. 13 Field making a first-round trip to No. 4 Alliance.
From the Suburban American, No. 10 Roosevelt visits No. 7 Wadsworth Feb. 27 with the winner traveling to No. 2 Copley March 2. The Rough Riders haven’t played the Grizzlies this season. They fell to the Indians, 67-43, Jan. 11, and are set to travel to Copley for their final Suburban American battle Feb. 22.<|end_of_text|>We collect information from you when you order on our site, contact us via forms or enter information on our site.
All transactions are processed through Microsoft Azure, our provider.
This website contains links to other websites. And we are not responsible for the privacy policies or practices of any third party.
If at any time you would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, you can email us at info-(_sm3Remove)-_-(_a)-_haugen-gruppen-(d_)-_dk and we will promptly remove you from ALL correspondence.<|end_of_text|>MUMBAI (Reuters) - Foxconn Technology is in talks to manufacture Apple’s iPhone in India, government officials said, in a move that could lower prices in the world’s No.3 smartphone market where the U.S. firm trails Samsung Electronics and local players.
India could help Foxconn mitigate accelerating wage inflation in China, where it makes the majority of iPhones, and base production sites closer to markets where its key clients want to grow.
Lower production costs could also help Foxconn keep hold of Apple orders amid intensifying competition with nimble manufacturing rivals such as Quanta Computer Inc.
“Foxconn is sending a delegation of their officers to scout for locations in a month’s time,” Subhash Desai, Industries Minister of India’s western state Maharashtra, told Reuters.
Foxconn has said it is aiming to develop 10-12 facilities in India, including factories and data centers, by 2020, but had given no detail.
The Taiwan-based tech giant, the world’s largest contract maker of electronic products, declined to comment on detailed plans on Thursday, citing commercial sensitivity.
Apple representatives in India did not respond to a request for comment on Thursday.
Apple’s iPhone 6 with 16 GB sells for around 44,000 rupees ($687.82) in India, versus Samsung’s Galaxy S6 with 32 GB which sells for around 40,000 rupees ($625.29).
It has 10 percent market share in India, trailing Samsung and local manufacturers such as Micromax, which dominate the market, according to Counterpoint Research Market Monitor.
A return of Foxconn — which was forced to shut up shop in India last year after client Nokia closed — would be a major victory for India, which badly needs to turn its tech boom into a manufacturing and employment boost.
India, under Prime Minister Narendra Modi, has sought to reboot manufacturing, but the country is yet to rival China, particularly in technology where most factories will likely be assembly units to begin with.
Apple is among the biggest clients for Foxconn — the trade name for Hon Hai Precision Industry Co Ltd — which also makes components for companies such as Xiaomi, Acer and Sony.
“The smartphone boom in India indicates the time is just right to focus on expansion plans and increasing volume in India to a comparable level with the China market in the next five years,” said Sky Li, vice president of phone manufacturer OPPO.
India has the second-highest number of mobile phone accounts behind China. According to networking solutions company Cisco Systems, there will be 650 million smartphones in the country by 2019. The number of tablets will rise 9 percent to 18.7 million by then.<|end_of_text|>Original Scent Wood Cleaner & Preservative, 10-oz.
Time-tested organic oil penetrating action formula, safely cleans, shines, dusts, restores, and preserves all natural or unfinished wood. Also, helps preserve drying and cracking to wood caused by heating and air conditioning systems.<|end_of_text|>Amazon is offering a FREE Kindle download of Pilgrim’s Progress (Illustrated) right now.
