« FREE Bag of Purina One Dog or Cat Food!<|end_of_text|>Description This home is a handy man special & is priced to sell!!! Home has 3 bedrooms, 1 & 1/2 baths, new metal roof in October of 2017, furnace and A/C have been updated. Lots of character with old fashion woodwork on level lot with 1 & 1/2 car detached garage. Call for more details or a personal tour!!<|end_of_text|>This is a super simple rhubarb syrup- perfect for adding to a gin & tonic, vodka & lemonade or your favourite cocktail. Or, if you’re no fun, you could just make a nice alcohol-free pink lemonade with this. The flavour is light and sweet with a subtle rhubarb taste, not to mention how beautiful their light pink colour is. Add sunshine + friends + good music for extra enjoyment!
A flavourful rhubarb syrup & how to make a delicious gin & tonic with it.
Combine syrup ingredients in a sauce pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer and cook until fruit is softened, about 20 minutes. Pour mixture through a strainer. Set aside to cool.
Combine gin, tonic, rhubarb syrup, squeeze of lime juice, and sprig of mint. Enjoy!
Try replacing some of the rhubarb with strawberries for a great flavour combination!<|end_of_text|>SACRAMENTO, Calif. — The Sacramento Kings hired Luke Walton as their coach Monday, just days after the Los Angeles Lakers parted ways with him following three losing seasons.
Neither the Kings nor Walton waited long following changes that came just after the end of the regular season. Sacramento fired coach Dave Joerger on Thursday following a 39-43 finish that was the best record for the franchise in 13 years, while Walton was dismissed in Los Angeles a day later when he failed to get the Lakers into the postseason in the first year with LeBron James.
Walton now takes over an up-and-coming team in Sacramento that features several talented young players acquired by Divac: guards De'Aaron Fox and Buddy Hield, forward Marvin Bagley III and center Willie Cauley-Stein. The Kings finished 39-43, nine games out of a playoff spot after being tied for the Western Conference's eighth seed heading into the final game before the All-Star break.<|end_of_text|>The Cream yadaBags Classic Purse was designed with pockets and dividers to organize your diabetics supplies with style!
